quran[67]{c,v,t}:
  90,1,I swear by this land
  90,2,and you are a resident of this land
  90,3,and by the father and what he fathered
  90,4,that We have certainly created the human being in distress
  90,5,Does he think that no one will ever have power over him
  90,6,"He says: I wasted a lot of wealth"
  90,7,Does he think that no one saw him
  90,8,Did we not make two eyes for him
  90,9,and a tongue and two lips
  90,10,and We guided him to the two ways
  90,11,But he did not take/attempt the winding mountain road
  90,12,And do you know what the winding mountain road is
  90,13,(It is) freeing a slave
  90,14,"or in a day of famine, feeding"
  90,15,an orphan being related
  90,16,or a poor person in ruins (and penniless)
  90,17,then being of those who believed and recommend one another to the perseverance (and patience) and recommend one another to kindness
  90,18,They are associates of the right hand (the fortunate)
  90,19,"And those who disbelieved in Our signs, they are associates of the left hand (the unfortunate)"
  90,20,and a fire is closed over upon them
  91,1,By the sun and its glow
  91,2,and by the moon when it follows it
  91,3,and by the day when it shows it
  91,4,and by the night when it covers it
  91,5,and by the sky and what built it
  91,6,and the earth and what extended it
  91,7,and by the soul and what shaped it
  91,8,and inspired it to its immoralities and its self control
  91,9,"(that) anyone who purifies it, has succeeded"
  91,10,"and anyone who corrupts it, has failed"
  91,11,Thamud denied with their rebellion
  91,12,When the most nasty of them rose up
  91,13,"then God's messenger said to them: (that is) God's female camel and her share of drink"
  91,14,"Then they denied him and killed her, then their Master fully punished them for their sins and leveled them (to the ground)"
  91,15,and He was not afraid of its outcome
  92,1,By the night when it covers
  92,2,and by the day when it shows
  92,3,and by what created the male and the female
  92,4,indeed your efforts are different
  92,5,As for anyone who gives and controls himself
  92,6,and confirms the goodness
  92,7,then We are going to get him ready for the easy way
  92,8,And as for anyone who is stingy and supposes he has no need
  92,9,and denies the goodness
  92,10,then We are going to get him ready for the difficult way
  92,11,and his wealth will be of no use when he falls (dead)
  92,12,Indeed the guidance is Our responsibility
  92,13,And the hereafter and the first (this world) belong to Us
  92,14,So I warn you of a flaming fire
  92,15,no one enters (and burns in) it except the most unfortunate
  92,16,the one who denied and turned away
  92,17,And the more cautious (of God) are going to be kept away from it
  92,18,The one who gives his wealth to be purified
  92,19,And no one has any favor with Him to be rewarded (for it)
  92,20,"except (anyone who) looks for the attention (and pleasure) of his Master, the highest"
  92,21,and he is going to be pleased
  93,1,By the daylight
  93,2,and by the night when it quiets
  93,3,(that) your Master did not abandon you and He is not upset
  93,4,And the hereafter is certainly better for you than the first (this life)
  93,5,And your Master will certainly give you (enough) so you are pleased
  93,6,Did He not find you an orphan and sheltered you
  93,7,and found you a lost one and guided you
  93,8,and found you in need and made you needless
  93,9,"As for the orphan, do not mistreat them"
  93,10,"And as for the one who asks (the beggar), do not drive them away"
  93,11,"And as for the favor of your Master, speak of it"